               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18120513-72-person748">
                  THOMAS 
                  BROWN
               <interp inst="t18120513-72-person748" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120513-72-person748" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120513-72-person748" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a mathematical-instrument-maker. I dealt with Mr. Christie for bread. On the 25th of March three loaves of bread were owing from me. I paid for them to the prisoner. I gave him a pound note, and he gave me change. I am quite sure I paid him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18120513-72-person749">
                  WILLIAM 
                  CHRISTIE
               <interp inst="t18120513-72-person749" type="surname" value="CHRISTIE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120513-72-person749" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120513-72-person749" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 25th the prisoner did not account for any money received that day from Mr. Brown. When the prisoner accounted to me, my apprentice made the entries in this book.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18120513-72-person750">
                  JOHN 
                  BULLEYMAN
               <interp inst="t18120513-72-person750" type="surname" value="BULLEYMAN"></interp>
